	demonstrator. TAs and demonstrators are
	there to help!
      </p> 

  
    

    
      <h3 class="head"><a name="section-2">Exercise 1</a></h3>
      <p>
	In this exercise we want you to develop a program that allows
	the user to enter the details of their favourite male and female
	movie popstars.
      </p>

      <p>
        The information is gathered via the <code>Scanner</code> class
	and the output via the <code>System.out.println</code> method.
      </p>

      <p>
       Structure your program in the following way:
       </p><ol>
         <li> Create variables to store the information provided by
         the user. Decide what datatype is required for each
         variable. </li>
         <li> Prompt the user for the first name, surname
         and age of the male popstar. Store the information given in the prepared
         variables </li>
         <li> Create an instance of the <code>Person2</code> class with the
         information stored in the variables </li>
         <li>  Prompt the user for the first name, surname
         and age of the female popstar. Store the information given in the prepared
         variables </li>         
          <li> Create another instance of the <code>Person2</code>
         class with the
         information stored in the variables </li>
         <li> Print out the information of the two instances of the
         <code> Person2 </code> class. </li>
       </ol>
      

      <p>
        <span style="color:red"> Consult </span> the <a href="classes/Person2.html" shape="rect"> Person2
         class Documentation</a>.
      </p>

      

      <p> <strong>  It is important to prompt the user for the
		information in the following order.
	    </strong>

          </p><p> Example run: </p>
	  <pre xml:space="preserve">

	    Please enter the firstname of your favourite male popstar
            (User enters &quot;Justin&quot;)

            Please enter the Surname of your favourite male popstar
            (User enters &quot;Timberlake&quot;)

            Please enter the age of your favourite male popstar
            (User enters 33)

            Please enter the firstname of your favourite female popstar
            (User enters &quot;Britney&quot;)

            Please enter the Surname of your favourite female popstar
            (User enters &quot;Spears&quot;)

            Please enter the age of your favourite female popstar
            (User enters 32)

            Your favourite actor is FirstName: Justin
            Surname: Timberlake
            Age: 33
            Gender: male

            Your favourite actress is FirstName: Britney
            Surname: Spears
            Age: 32
            Gender: female

           </pre>
    
        
      <p>
	Compile and run the application and then submit it.
      </p>
      

    

    
      <h3 class="head"><a name="section-3">Exercise 2</a></h3>


      <p>
        One aim in this exercise is to write a program without a
        provided skeleton program. 
      </p>

      <p>
        A company refunds travel expenses for their staff. It uses the
        following formulas to calculate the price for using the train
        and the price for using the car. 
      </p>
      <p> Train price = 60 + (2/10) * distance in miles
      </p>
      <p> Car price = 25 + (7/10) * distance in miles
      </p>

      <p> For any given distance the company only refunds either the
      train or the car price, what ever is cheaper. 
      Also, each staff member has to cover a certain percentage of the
      cost. So the refund is calculated by taking the cheapest of the
      car or train price and then multiplying it with (100- self
      contribution)/100.
      </p>
   
     <p>
     <strong>Example:</strong> A distance of 100 miles would have a train price of 80 and car
     a price of 95. A staff member with a self contribution of 20 would get a
     refund of 80% of 80, which is 64.
     </p>  

     <p>
       Your task is to write a program that first asks the user for
       the distance and then for the self contribution. The program
       finishes by printing out the amount of refund the member of
       staff gets.
     </p>
  <p> <strong>  It is important to prompt the user for the
		information in the following order.
	    </strong>

          </p><p> Example run: </p>
	  <pre xml:space="preserve">

          Please enter the distance:
          (User enters 30)

          Please enter the percentage of self contribution:
          (User enters 60)

          You get a refund of 18.4
          </pre>
    
        

      <p>
          You can assume that the distance is entered to the nearest
          mile and that the percentage of self contribution is a whole
          number between 0 and 100.
      </p>


      <p>
         Hints:

         </p><ol>
           <li> 
              Use the application template by following the description
              in the file.
           </li>
           <li>
              Prepare variables of the right data type and create
              an instance of the <code> Scanner </code> class.
           </li>
           <li>
              Collect the input from the <code> Scanner </code> class
           instance and store it in the variables.
           </li>  
           <li>
              Calculate the refund (probably in multiple steps) and
              store the result in a variable
           </li>
           <li>
              Print out the result.
           </li>
           
         </ol>
         The exercise can and should be completed without the use of an
         'if' statement, which will be introduced in the following weeks.
      
   

